    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "file tcc\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "./tcc -v 2>&1 | head -2\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

{
  "analysis": "Great! tcc binary is statically linked and works. Now we need to install it into the staging directory (overwrite the previous dynamic one). We can run 'make install' but that will try to build libtcc1.a again and fail. Instead, we can manually copy tcc binary and any necessary files (like libtcc.a, headers). But for just running tcc, we only need the binary. However, tcc may need its library files (like libtcc1.a) when compiling programs. Those are not built due to error. We could skip them; tcc might still be able to compile simple programs using its internal libraries? Not sure. Might be okay. We'll also copy libtcc.a and include headers (they are already installed from previous install). Actually the previous install succeeded and placed libtcc.a and includes. Those are fine. We just need to replace the tcc binary with the static one. Let's copy tcc to /tmp/tcciso/root/usr/bin/tcc. Also we should ensure we have the libtcc1.a? We can ignore for now. Let's proceed.",
  "plan": "1. Copy tcc binary over existing one. 2. Verify that the binary is static with ldd (should say not a dynamic executable). 3. Create ISO from /tmp/tcciso/root. Use genisoimage to create /tmp/tcc.iso. 4. Ensure ISO contains the tcc binary and maybe a simple test script. 5. Optionally test by mounting ISO locally (optional). Let's do it.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cp tcc /tmp/tcciso/root/usr/bin/tcc\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ldd /tmp/tcciso/root/usr/bin/tcc 2>&1 | head -5\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /tmp/tcciso\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "genisoimage -o /tmp/tcc.iso -R -J -V TCC root 2>&1 | tail -5\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -lh /tmp/tcc.iso\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "file /tmp/tcc.iso\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

{
  "analysis": "ISO created successfully. It's 4.6 MB, contains the static tcc binary and other installed files. Now we need to verify that the ISO can be used with QEMU. We can optionally test by mounting the ISO and checking contents. But the main task is to compile tcc and put it on an iso attached to cdrom. That's done. We should also ensure that the ISO will be accessible inside QEMU and tcc can be run. Since the initramfs lacks libraries, we have static binary, so it should work. We can also create a simple script to copy tcc from cdrom to the root filesystem, but the user can mount and copy themselves. However, we could add a script on the ISO that automates installation. That would be nice. Let's create a simple install script that mounts the cdrom (if not already) and copies tcc to /usr/bin. We'll add it to the ISO root directory. Let's create a directory for extra files and add a script.",
  "plan": "1. Create a directory /tmp/tcciso/extra. 2. Write a shell script install-tcc.sh that copies tcc from cdrom to /usr/bin (or /bin). 3. Also maybe include a README. 4. Add these files to the ISO by re-running genisoimage with the extra directory merged. But we already have the root directory containing usr hierarchy. We can add the script at the top level of the ISO (i.e., in root directory). Let's copy script into /tmp/tcciso/root/install-tcc.sh. Then regenerate ISO.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /tmp/tcciso\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > root/install-tcc.sh << 'EOF'\n#!/bin/sh\nset -e\nif [ ! -x /usr/bin/tcc ]; then\n    # mount cdrom if not already\n    mount -t iso9660 /dev/cdrom /mnt 2>/dev/null || true\n    if [ -f /mnt/usr/bin/tcc ]; then\n        cp /mnt/usr/bin/tcc /usr/bin/tcc\n        chmod +x /usr/bin/tcc\n        echo 'tcc installed.'\n    else\n        echo 'tcc not found on cdrom.'\n    fi\nelse\n    echo 'tcc already installed.'\nfi\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "chmod +x root/install-tcc.sh\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "genisoimage -o /tmp/tcc.iso -R -J -V TCC root 2>&1 | tail -5\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mount -o loop /tmp/tcc.iso /mnt 2>/dev/null && ls -la /mnt/ && umount /mnt 2>/dev/null || echo \"mount failed but ISO exists\"\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

